{{Infobox hieroglyphs
|NAME = <hiero>F27-F27-T19-T19 N14 N33*N33:N33:N33</hiero>
|NAME-TRANSKRIPTION = Septi-chenwi<br/>''Sp.tj-ḥn.wj''<br/>''The Two Fishes''
}}

'''Septi-chenwi''' is the designation of an [[:en:Ancient Egypt|Ancient Egypt]] [[:en:Decan|Decan]], which comprised four {{ill|Baktiu|1=Baktiu|2=de|3=Baktiu|de|Baktiu|1=Baktiu|2=de|3=Baktiu|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baktiu|qq=}} (decan stars).

The most prominent [[:en:Star|Star]]s of this decan are {{ill|Delta Sagittarii|de|Delta Sagittarii|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Delta Sagittarii|qq=}} (Kaus Medius) in the [[:en:Sagittarius (constellation)|Sagittarius (constellation)]] constellation, as well as [[:en:Delta Ophiuchi|Delta Ophiuchi]] and [[:en:Epsilon Ophiuchi|Epsilon Ophiuchi]] (Yed Prior and Yed Posterior) in the constellation [[:en:Ophiuchus|Ophiuchus]].

In the decan lists of the {{ill|Book of Nut#Pharaonic period|lt=Pharaonic period|de|Nutbuch#Pharaonische Zeit|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Book of Nut#Pharaonic period|qq=}}, Septi-chenwi represented the 13th decan on the body of {{ill|Nut (Egyptian mythology)|de|Nut (Ägyptische Mythologie)|1=Nut (goddess)|lt=Nut|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nut (Egyptian mythology)|13=User:Immanuelle/Nut (goddess)|qq=}}. The [[:en:Heliacal rising|Heliacal rising]] was set for the {{ill|Achet#Dating|lt=6th Achet I|de|6. Achet I|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Achet#Dating|qq=}}, based on the arrangement ordered under [[:en:Senusret III|Senusret III]] ([[:en:Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt]]) in his seventh year of reign.

== Literature ==
* [[:en:Christian Leitz|Christian Leitz]]: ''Altägyptische Sternuhren''. Peeters, Leuven 1995, ISBN 90-6831-669-9, p. 90.  
* {{ill|Alexandra von Lieven|fr|Alexandra von Lieven|de|Alexandra von Lieven|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Alexandra von Lieven|qq=}}: ''Grundriss des Laufes der Sterne – Das sogenannte Nutbuch''. The Carsten Niebuhr Institute of Ancient Eastern Studies (et al.), Copenhagen 2007, ISBN 978-87-635-0406-5, pp. 62–67 and 385.

{{translated page|de|Septi-chenwi|version=|comment=Imported full de history, revisions duplicated and version not here due to an error with my bot related to the German being under the same pagename as the english}}

